0~COMDCMDTDElement~2~1#=GlobalID~Global/Parameter~6~30~~~~~~~~~~~This field is used to associate the DTD with the source data. As a DTD can be used for either foreign location method invocation or detailed breakdown of complex field structures, the entry here is either the associated parameter name or the assigned Global node literal. e.g.||Foreign Location Invocation DTD|   saveCompany Event with fields (CompanyNo, CompanyName) invokes the recordCompany Method with parameters (ID, Name).|In the Global/Parameter field you would enter "ID" for the Company number element, and "Name" for the Company name element.||Complex Data Type Breakdown|   The global is structured as follows:|^SaleDetails("H",SaleNo)=header record|^SaleDetails("H",SaleNo,"L",LineNo)=line 1 details|In the Global/Parameter field you would enter "H" for the header element, and "L" for the Line element. N.B. no entry should be made for the leaf elements, i.e. those elements without children, as they are accessed via the field sequence in the node value.|~~~~~~~~~~GlobalID~~~~~~~~~~~

0~INSYSLOG~4~1#=Internal Project Flags  ~Internal Project Flags  ~6~30~~4~~WWW101~"SYSAKTION",SPRACHE~1~~~~~Da Änderungen von verschiedensprachigen Prozessen (je nach Aufrufer) gemacht werden können, ist ein Sprachentext nicht gut für eine spätere Suche.
